Allophones

The [voiced bilabial plosive](/Voiced_bilabial_plosive) /b/ is phonetically realized as a [voiced labial approximant](/Voiced_bilabial_approximant) [β̞] when it occurs medially between [sonorants](/Sonorant) and is not [geminated](/Gemination). The fricative ejective /[sʼ](/Alveolar_ejective_fricative)/ is often perceived as an affricate sound [[t͡sʼ](/Alveolar_ejective_affricate)], though it is phonemically a fricative ejective. The [rhotic consonant](/Rhotic_consonant) is realized as a [trill](/Voiced_alveolar_trill) when geminated and as a [tap](/Voiced_alveolar_tap) when not. The [closed central unrounded vowel](/Close_central_unrounded_vowel) &#x27e8;ə&#x27e9; /ɨ/ and the [mid-central vowel](/Mid_central_vowel) &#x27e8;ä&#x27e9; /ə/ tend to be fronted to [[ɪ](/Near-close_near-front_unrounded_vowel)] and [[ɛ](/Open-mid_front_unrounded_vowel)], respectively, when they follow [palatal consonants](/Palatal_consonant). Conversely, they are retracted and rounded to [[ʊ](/Near-close_near-back_rounded_vowel)] and [[ɔ](/Open-mid_back_rounded_vowel)], respectively, after [labialized velar consonants](/Labialized_velar_consonant). &#91;55&#93;

