[Semitic languages](/Semitic_languages)
Branches: East, West, Central, South.
East: [Akkadian](/Akkadian_language), [Eblaite](/Eblaite_language).
Central: [Arabic](/Arabic), [Aramaic](/Aramaic), [Hebrew](/Hebrew_language).
South: Southeast ([Baṭḥari](/Ba%E1%B9%AD%E1%B8%A5ari_language), [Mehri](/Mehri_language), etc.), Southwest ([Abyssinian](/Abyssinian_languages) - North: [Geʽez](/Ge%CA%BDez), [Tigre](/Tigre_language), [Tigrinya](/Tigrinya_language); South: Transversal ([Amharic](/Amharic_language)–[Argobba](/Argobba_language), [Harari](/Harari_language)–[East Gurage](/Gurage_people)), Outer ([Gafat](/Gafat_language), [Soddo](/Soddo_language), etc.), West Gurage). Sayhadic ([Faifi](/Faifi_language), [Sabaic](/Sabaic), etc.).
Historical: [Proto-Semitic](/Proto-Semitic_language).